## Concepts Practiced

| Concept | Used In |
|---|---|
| `argparse` CLI arguments | `main.py` |
| Exception handling | `main.py` |
| Regex with capture groups | `analyzer.py` |
| `defaultdict(int/list)` | `analyzer.py` |
| Dict comprehension | `analyzer.py` |
| JSON output with `json.dump` | `report.py` |
| Compromise detection logic | `report.py` |

---

## Security Relevance

SSH brute force is one of the most common attack vectors against exposed servers. This tool replicates the core detection logic used in real SIEM systems and IDS tools like Fail2Ban — parse logs, count failures per source, alert on threshold breach, flag successful logins from attacking IPs as high-severity compromise indicators.

